Meanings":[{"name":"Lascelles","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from one of the large number of places in northern France called Celle, Celles, Lacelle, Leschelle, or Lachelle, all from French <i>celle</i> ‘hermitage’, and at different times occurring both with and without the plural <i>-s</i>.","Variant of   Lacelle   1, a surname of French origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Laswell","meanings":["English: possibly an altered form of   Lascelles  . This surname is also found as   Lacefield  ."]},{"name":"Lasell","meanings":["English: variant of   Lascelles  ."]},{"name":"Lacelle","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alain, Andre, Aurele, Benoit, Cecile, Marcel, Marie Paule.","Altered form of French <b>Laselle</b>: habitational name from La Selle, the name of several places in various parts of France. The surname <i>Laselle</i> is very rare in France, found in Marne. Compare   Lascelles  .","In some cases possibly also French: habitational name from Lacelle in Corrèze or numerous minor places called La Celle, all named for a monastic cell or hermitage in their vicinity, from French <i>celle</i> ‘hermitage’."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Lascelles was born in 1286, in England, United Kingdom. She married Alexander de Stanhope in 1300, in Stanhope, Durham, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1286–":"1286–Surnud","1270–1360":"1270–1360","1300–1376":"1300–1376","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1286–Female":"1286–Surnud","1300":"1300","1376":"1376","1286":"1286","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1390":"1390","Stanhope, Weardale, Durham, England":"Stanhope, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stanhope Castle, Stanhope, Durham, England":"Stanhope, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1286–":"1286–Kuollut","1270–1360":"1270–1360","1300–1376":"1300–1376","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1286–Female":"1286–Kuollut","1300":"1300","1376":"1376","1286":"1286","about 1300":"noin 1300","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1390":"1390","Stanhope, Weardale, Durham, England":"Stanhope, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stanhope Castle, Stanhope, Durham, England":"Stanhope, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1286–":"1286–Décédée","1270–1360":"1270–1360","1300–1376":"1300–1376","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1286–Female":"1286–Décédée","1300":"1300","1376":"1376","1286":"1286","about 1300":"environ 1300","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1390":"1390","Stanhope, Weardale, Durham, England":"Stanhope, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Stanhope Castle, Stanhope, Durham, England":"Stanhope, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Agnes Lascelles est née en 1286, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Alexander de Stanhope en 1300, à Stanhope, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille."},"de":{"1286–":"1286–Verstorben","1270–1360":"1270–1360","1300